h detailed information about each writer from David Perell's interviews. Using Tool | Set Header Titles Now I'll populate the table with comprehensive data for each writer from David Perell's interviews. Let me start with the first few rows using the detailed information I've gathered. Using Tool | Update Cells Set row 1: Video URL = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mqupPpnGtP8, Video Title = How to Actually Think About Writing with AI — Jimmy Soni, Video Description = I interviewed Jimmy Soni, who is currently writing a book about Kobe Bryant. He spent six years on his previous book about the origin story of PayPal and the entrepreneurs who shaped Silicon Valley., Writer's Name = Jimmy Soni, Publication Date = 3 days ago, Video Length = 1:30:48, View Count = 4823, Set row 1: Writer's Major Publications = A Mind at Play (Claude Shannon biography), The Founders (PayPal story), Rome's Last Citizen (Cato biography), Writing Category/Niche = Biography/Business History, Career Background = Former Huffington Post managing editor, speechwriter, strategy consultant at McKinsey, worked for Mayor of DC, Set row 1: Writing Process & Methods = Six-year deep research cycles, extensive interviews with primary sources, narrative non-fiction approach combining historical rigor with storytelling accessibility, meticulous fact-checking and verification processes, Research Methodology = Primary source interviews, archival research, corporate document analysis, multiple verification sources, immersive subject study, Set row 1: Key Influences & Inspirations = Historical figures who shaped technology and business, intersection of biography and business history, stories of innovation and entrepreneurship, Unique Techniques = Novelistic storytelling techniques applied to non-fiction, character-driven narratives in business contexts, extensive use of dialogue and scene-setting, Set row 1: Writing Philosophy = Make complex business and technical stories accessible to general audiences, reveal