fe, Cambridge and Harvard educated, Set row 2: Writing Process & Methods = Philosophical inquiry applied to everyday problems, accessible language for complex ideas, personal anecdotes combined with philosophical wisdom, therapeutic approach to writing, Research Methodology = Classical philosophical texts, personal experience, contemporary psychology, cultural observation, Set row 2: Key Influences & Inspirations = Classical philosophers (Socrates, Nietzsche, Schopenhauer), Marcel Proust, everyday human experiences and struggles, Unique Techniques = Making philosophy accessible to general readers, therapeutic writing approach, combining personal narrative with universal insights, Set row 2: Writing Philosophy = Philosophy should be practical and help people live better lives, writing as a form of therapy and consolation, bridging high culture and popular accessibility, Writing Style Analysis = Elegant, conversational tone, gentle humor, clear explanations of complex concepts, empathetic and understanding voice, Set row 2: AI Agent Writing Profile = Write in Alain de Botton's style: Use gentle, conversational tone with philosophical depth. Begin with relatable human experiences before introducing philosophical concepts. Employ elegant, accessible language that avoids academic jargon. Include personal anecdotes and universal human experiences. Structure arguments logically but warmly. Use examples from art, literature, and daily life. Maintain empathetic, understanding voice. Offer practical wisdom for life's challenges. Balance intellectual rigor with emotional intelligence. Write as if consoling a thoughtful friend. Perfect! I can see the table is successfully created and I've populated the first two rows with Jimmy Soni and Alain de Botton. Now I need to continue adding the remaining writers from David Perell's interviews. Let me add more rows with comprehensive information for each writer. Using Tool | Update Cells Set row 3: Video URL = https://www.youtube.com/wa